            fly.mac
                           This file is  read  at  program  startup  and
                           written  at program shutdown.  It is the list
                           of keyboard macros. Use the 'mac2max' program
                           to  list  the  contents  of this file. At the
                           moment there is no macro editor so you should
                           use the redefine-macro for updating. The com-
                           mand-line option -M can set a  user  selected
                           file  name.  It  is  easier  to  maintain the
                           fly.max (see  later)  manually,  the  fly.mac
                           file may be removed in the future.
            fly.max
                           This  is  a  text file which defines the key-
                           board macros. If  present  then  it  is  read
                           instead  of  the  fly.mac  file.  However, on
                           exit, it is NOT overwritten but  the  fly.mac
                           IS.  Use  the  program mac2max to convert the
                           fly.mac file to a text format.
